17.
Job description
Its fun to work in a company where people truly BELIEVE in what they are doing!


Were committed to bringing passion and customer focus to the business.


Healthcare Data & Business Consultant

Responsibilities

The Healthcare Data & Business Consultant will play a key role in leading and supporting consulting engagements across the healthcare domain with a strong focus on data engineering, modernization, and enablement. The consultant will bridge the gap between business and technology translating healthcare business needs into data-driven architectures, models, and solutions that drive measurable outcomes. This role will also contribute to capability building and business growth initiatives across the healthcare vertical.

Key Responsibilities:

Business Consulting & Data Solutioning:
Engage with healthcare clients (payer, provider, PBM, life sciences, etc.) to understand their business challenges and translate them into data engineering and modernization opportunities. Define solution architectures and data strategies for use cases such as claims integration, member360, provider network design, utilization management, and care coordination.

Healthcare Data Management & Engineering:
Work with cross-functional data teams to design and implement robust data pipelines, data lakes, and data warehouses. Be able to curate ingestion, transformation, and curation of logic across layers working with Engineering teams. Support the design of scalable data models that unify medical, pharmacy, provider, and member data.

Data Modernization & Cloud Enablement:
Partner with technology teams to implement modern data platforms, leveraging tools such as Power BI, Databricks, Azure. Contribute to the development of frameworks for data quality, metadata management, lineage, and governance aligned with healthcare compliance (HIPAA, HITRUST).

Solution Development & Enablement:
Support internal capability teams in building healthcare-specific accelerators and reusable components for data ingestion, processing, and quality management. Contribute to proposals and client discussions by framing data-led transformation roadmaps and architecture blueprints.

Client Engagement & Growth:
Work closely with sales and delivery teams to identify opportunities for data modernization within existing or new healthcare accounts. Participate in client workshops, pre-sales conversations, and proposal creation by providing domain depth in healthcare data ecosystems.
Qualification & Experience

Minimum 5 years of experience in healthcare, data management, or consulting roles
Strong understanding of healthcare data ecosystems (claims, clinical, member, provider, EHR, HEDIS, or quality measures)
Hands-on exposure to data platforms and tools (Power BI, SQL, Databricks, Azure Data Factory or similar)
Knowledge of data governance, data quality, and interoperability standards (FHIR, HL7, HIPAA compliance) preferred
Excellent problem-solving, healthcare data understanding, business communication, and stakeholder management skills
Education:
Bachelor s degree in engineering (BE/BTech) or equivalent; advanced degree (MBA, MPH, or related) preferred.



If you like wild growth and working with happy, enthusiastic over-achievers, youll enjoy your career with us!


